1
00:00:01,376 --> 00:00:04,254
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:25,877 --> 00:01:27,504
DECEMBER 2007

3
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,381
[Mello] What was that? Roger?

4
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:30,674
What did you just say?

5
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:35,220
I'm afraid L is dead.

6
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:37,931
He's dead?

7
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:39,600
But... but how?

8
00:01:41,893 --> 00:01:43,645
Was it Kira? Did Kira kill him?

9
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:45,689
Come on, Roger. You've got to tell me.

10
00:01:46,148 --> 00:01:47,149
[Roger] Probably.

11
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:49,776
But he promised me he'd find Kira
and execute him,

12
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:51,153
and now you're telling me

13
00:01:51,236 --> 00:01:52,487
that he's been killed?

14
00:01:53,071 --> 00:01:54,615
-[Roger] Mello…
-[clatter]

15
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:55,699
[Mello] Huh?

16
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:05,250
[Near] If you can't win the game…

17
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:07,961
If you can't solve the puzzle…

18
00:02:09,338 --> 00:02:10,756
Then you're just a loser.

19
00:02:12,841 --> 00:02:13,759
[grunts]

20
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:17,512
So, which of us did L pick?
Me or Near?

21
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:22,142
He hadn't chosen yet.

22
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:23,894
And now that he's gone,

23
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:25,729
I'm afraid he won't be able to.

24
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,065
[Mello] Uh...

25
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,358
Mello.

26
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:30,734
Listen.

27
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:32,277
You too, Near.

28
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,446
Can't the two of you work together?

29
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:36,490
All right. Sounds good.

30
00:02:41,078 --> 00:02:42,621
[Mello] It'll never work, Roger.

31
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,414
We can't do this together.

32
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:46,458
You know I don't get along with Near.

33
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:49,169
We've always competed against each other.

34
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:50,837
Always!

35
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:53,674
[wind howling outside]

36
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,811
You know what? It's fine.

37
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:06,812
Huh?

38
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:09,356
Near should be the one to succeed L.

39
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,900
He is not like me.
He never gets emotional,

40
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,360
he just uses his head,

41
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:15,153
like it's a game or a puzzle.

42
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:19,408
And as for me...

43
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:22,369
I'm leaving this institution.

44
00:03:22,494 --> 00:03:23,745
Wait, Mello!

45
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:26,540
[Mello] Don't waste your breath.
I'm almost fifteen years old.

46
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:27,499
[door creaks]

47
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:30,460
[Mello] It's time I started living
my own life.

48
00:03:37,406 --> 00:03:38,282
MARCH 5, 2012

49
00:03:38,382 --> 00:03:40,762
[Near] A police officer who happened
to be nearby during Higuchi's arrest,

50
00:03:40,846 --> 00:03:42,806
overheard him talking about the notebook,

51
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:45,684
If you write a person's name in it
with their face in mind,

52
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:46,977
that person will die.

53
00:03:47,144 --> 00:03:50,439
So that's what you're saying
this notebook of death actually is?

54
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:51,606
[Near] That's right.

55
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:54,818
At this point the Japanese police
should have it in their possession.

56
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:58,085
A YOUNG MAN NAMED NEAR PRESENTS
EVIDENCE ON THE KIRA CASE

57
00:03:58,193 --> 00:04:01,992
WHICH HE'S GATHERED BY HIMSELF
OVER THE LAST THREE YEARS.

58
00:04:02,114 --> 00:04:05,746
HE MEETS WITH THE PRESIDENT,
ACCOMPANIED BY THE DIRECTOR OF THE FBI.

59
00:04:06,163 --> 00:04:08,248
Mr. President, the current L is a fake.

60
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,000
He was created by the Japanese police

61
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,460
to avoid confusion and panic

62
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:13,962
amongst the various
international police agencies.

63
00:04:14,129 --> 00:04:15,714
The real L is dead.

64
00:04:16,131 --> 00:04:17,507
Director Mason…

65
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:19,009
This boy...

66
00:04:19,426 --> 00:04:20,510
Who is he?

67
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:21,845
Sir...

68
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,347
Near is... Well, in a sense
you could call him...

69
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:26,266
the true successor to L.

70
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:29,728
THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA

71
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:34,858
CREATES THEIR OWN INVESTIGATION TEAM
INDEPENDENT OF L TO GO AFTER KIRA.

72
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,068
THE SPK
(SPECIAL PROVISION FOR KIRA)

73
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:41,323
IS COMPOSED OF HAND-PICKED
FBI AND CIA AGENTS ALONG WITH NEAR.

74
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:47,329
ABDUCTION

75
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:53,084
[Yagami] But still, it's impossible for us
to censor everything on the internet.

76
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:55,629
And we haven't had
any new leads in a while.

77
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:59,716
But posting names and faces online?
I'm sorry, but if you ask me,

78
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,843
it's the people doing that
who deserve to die.

79
00:05:01,927 --> 00:05:02,803
[Yagami grunts]

80
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,471
But I guess...

81
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:06,014
that's never gonna happen.

82
00:05:06,097 --> 00:05:08,141
Kira gets a lot of his information
from the internet,

83
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,601
so he's not gonna kill those people.

84
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:13,271
[giggles] Matsu, you silly,
you've got it all backwards.

85
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:15,857
[Light] Still, I can imagine
how some people must feel.

86
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:20,028
To them, the world's become a good place
for people who don't commit any crimes.

87
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:23,657
Or rather, it's a good place
for innocent people who lead good lives.

88
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:26,034
[Ryuk cackles]
Look who's talking.

89
00:05:26,368 --> 00:05:27,285
It's more than that.

90
00:05:27,369 --> 00:05:30,121
Soon everyone in the world
will think that way.

91
00:05:30,747 --> 00:05:33,208
Are you all still talking
about that Kira business?

92
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,545
Please, give it a rest
for one afternoon, dear.

93
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:38,129
-Light, you too.
-[Sayu] I'm home.

94
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:39,464
-Huh?
-[door opens]

95
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:41,925
Hey, how's it going? [giggles]

96
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,343
We were just having tea.

97
00:05:43,552 --> 00:05:45,595
Oh, Light, Misa.

98
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:48,056
-Seems like it's been forever, you two.
-[Matsuda gasps]

99
00:05:48,223 --> 00:05:49,224
Missed you guys.

100
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:50,725
Aw, we missed you too.

101
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,312
And you must be... Mr. Matsuda, right?

102
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:55,605
Oh, that's me!

103
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:57,274
Wow, it's been a long time.

104
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,609
Thank you for always
taking such good care of my father.

105
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:01,653
[stammering] Geez, Sayu...

106
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:03,613
You're all grown up...

107
00:06:03,947 --> 00:06:04,865
and pretty.

108
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,325
Last time I saw you, you were this big...

109
00:06:07,409 --> 00:06:10,370
[Misa laughs] Matsu, your face
is going bright red!

110
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,330
It is? I mean... no way!

111
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:13,665
Well, you can forget it.

112
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:15,333
I'll never let Sayu marry a cop.

113
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,252
-Huh?
-Yes. That's right.

114
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:18,962
I'd never want that for my daughter.

115
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:20,964
-Really? Oh, man.
-[Misa giggles]

116
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:24,259
I never got the chance to propose,
or even tell her I like her.

117
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:26,595
You're too cruel to me, Mom and Dad.

118
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:27,679
-"Mom"?
-"Dad"?

119
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:31,016
Anyway, I think you'd be
a good catch, Mr. Matsuda.

120
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,183
What?

121
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:34,185
You really think so, Sayu?

122
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:38,064
Yep. In fact, I was thinking
if you were a little younger,

123
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:40,734
I might have considered
going out with you sometime.

124
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,193
[Matsuda cries]

125
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:44,279
Guess my little sister
is all grown up, isn't she?

126
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:45,739
[Misa] No kidding.

127
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:48,533
-She's already way more mature than Matsu.
-[Yagami scoffs]

128
00:06:48,992 --> 00:06:50,410
But of course,
Light hasn't changed one bit.

129
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:53,538
You're just as wonderful and handsome
as when I first met you.

130
00:06:54,164 --> 00:06:56,041
You've already got
a career and everything.

131
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:57,292
Make it official.

132
00:06:57,417 --> 00:07:00,295
You should stop living together secretly
and just get married already.

133
00:07:00,462 --> 00:07:02,047
I think that's a great idea.

134
00:07:02,464 --> 00:07:03,840
[cackles]

135
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:05,258
A heart-warming scene

136
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:07,802
from the most unfortunate family
in the world.

137
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,387
-[phone ringing]
-Huh?

138
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,265
[phone ringing]

139
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,935
Yes? What is it, Aizawa?

140
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,563
-Huh?
-[Light and Matsuda] Hm?

141
00:07:19,731 --> 00:07:20,607
Yes.

142
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:24,069
All right. Okay.

143
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:26,571
We have to go.

144
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,907
Matsuda, Light, come with me.

145
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:35,580
[Light] A kidnapping?

146
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:37,290
Involving who?

147
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,960
They got Director Takimura of the NPA.

148
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:41,628
Not sure who's behind it.

149
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,046
Ah, damn it!

150
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,924
As if we don't have enough
on our plate already with the Kira case.

151
00:07:50,025 --> 00:07:51,596
DEPUTY DIRECTOR

152
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,014
[Yagami] Are you sure about this?

153
00:07:53,515 --> 00:07:54,975
Unfortunately, yeah.

154
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,434
We got the phone call at 6:12.

155
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:58,019
That was about 45 minutes ago.

156
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,646
In the meantime, we were able to confirm

157
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:02,023
that the call originated
from the director's cell phone.

158
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:05,694
Did the kidnappers make any demands
in terms of ransom?

159
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,362
They did.

160
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:08,488
Huh?

161
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,116
They wanted to trade...

162
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:13,576
the director for the notebook.

163
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:17,205
[Light] Who's behind this?

164
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:18,456
And for what reason?

165
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:19,874
Do you think it's Kira?

166
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,585
Maybe not. If the existence
of the notebook has been leaked,

167
00:08:22,711 --> 00:08:24,963
there could be any number of people
who'd want it for themselves.

168
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:26,089
But hang on.

169
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:29,050
Dad, did you say anything to the director
about the notebook?

170
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:31,720
We all agreed to keep the information
between the six of us.

171
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,054
So, he didn't know, did he?

172
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:34,848
I never told the director,

173
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:36,766
so he couldn't tell the kidnappers
anything.

174
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,145
Someone knows about the Death Note.

175
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:41,396
And beyond that,

176
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,440
they know
that the Japanese police have it.

177
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:45,859
Now, they've come to claim it
for themselves.

178
00:08:46,735 --> 00:08:48,653
Notify every bureau
in the police department.

179
00:08:48,737 --> 00:08:51,531
-But only about the kidnapping itself.
-[Aizawa] Got it.

180
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:02,459
Hmm...

181
00:09:03,585 --> 00:09:05,545
-[phone beeping]
-[gasps]

182
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,381
Has there been a call from the suspects?

183
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,091
[Aizawa] No. There's a visitor here

184
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:12,135
who wants to meet
with the Director Takimura.

185
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:13,178
What?

186
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:15,764
[man] My name is John McEnroe,

187
00:09:16,056 --> 00:09:17,724
I'm an agent with the FBI.

188
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:19,642
Of course, this is just an alias.

189
00:09:19,768 --> 00:09:20,643
Uh...

190
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:22,771
As my assignment involves Kira,

191
00:09:22,854 --> 00:09:24,230
it's a necessary precaution.

192
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:25,482
Kira?

193
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:29,527
Due to unforeseen circumstances,
the director is unavailable.

194
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:32,363
If it's acceptable,
you can speak with me instead.

195
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,241
Very well, that's fine.

196
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:37,786
Pardon me, I'll get straight to the point.

197
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:40,538
Japanese police have proven themselves
to be unreliable.

198
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:41,706
[Yagami] Huh?

199
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,875
So, in order to solve the Kira case,

200
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,086
we want you to hand over
the notebook to us.

201
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,170
[gasps]

202
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,464
So the FBI was behind it?

203
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:51,382
Where did you take the director?

204
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:54,052
-[McEnroe] What are you talking about?
-[Yagami] Don't act like you don't know!

205
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,012
This is a serious criminal offense!

206
00:09:56,179 --> 00:09:57,555
[McEnroe] What would the FBI gain

207
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,100
by capturing the director
of the Japanese NPA?

208
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:02,143
What the hell is going on?

209
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,104
By the sound of things,

210
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:06,564
it seems that the director
of the Japanese police force

211
00:10:06,648 --> 00:10:08,566
-has been kidnapped by someone.
-[Rester groans]

212
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,069
Specifically, someone
who wants the notebook.

213
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:14,948
All right, Commander Rester.

214
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:15,990
Hmm?

215
00:10:16,074 --> 00:10:17,575
Pass on this message to our agent.

216
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:20,036
Suggest to the Japanese police
that we'd like to assist them

217
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:22,539
in rescuing the director
and apprehending the culprits.

218
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:25,041
We'll take the notebook
once we have the opportunity.

219
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,584
Roger that.

220
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:29,087
[Rester] Attention! This is headquarters.

221
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,131
We have new orders for you.

222
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:36,177
[footsteps echoing]

223
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,266
[metal door creaking]

224
00:10:41,391 --> 00:10:42,392
[director groans]

225
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:54,863
Has he decided to say anything yet?

226
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:56,364
He told us the Japanese police

227
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:58,074
had begun to wimp out on Kira,

228
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:01,327
Looks like right now
the only ones officially working for L

229
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:05,290
are Soichiro Yagami, Kanzo Mogi,
and Touta Matsuda.

230
00:11:05,373 --> 00:11:06,624
Isn't that right?

231
00:11:07,292 --> 00:11:08,251
Yeah.

232
00:11:08,877 --> 00:11:11,838
There was also Ukita,
but he was killed by Kira.

233
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:14,883
Right. And as a top cop
somehow you didn't know

234
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:16,551
that this notebook even existed,

235
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:17,802
or that you had it.

236
00:11:17,886 --> 00:11:21,264
[laughs]
Japanese cops must be a joke.

237
00:11:22,682 --> 00:11:24,767
Of all the investigators
on the task force,

238
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:27,812
Deputy Director Yagami
would be the highest ranking, right?

239
00:11:28,021 --> 00:11:29,189
[Takimura] Ye-- Yeah.

240
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:30,273
[scoffs]

241
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:36,446
My theory is that
there are two notebooks out there.

242
00:11:36,905 --> 00:11:38,781
One of them is in Kira's possession,

243
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,575
the other is with the NPA.

244
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,704
We're gonna take both of them.

245
00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:45,914
Huh?

246
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:46,956
Don't worry.

247
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,584
As long as we do what Mello says,
there will be no mistakes.

248
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:51,920
It's been a year and a half
since he joined us

249
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:54,923
and in that entire time
he's never been wrong about anything.

250
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:56,424
Yeah, but that's what's so weird.

251
00:11:56,549 --> 00:11:59,052
If he was able to bring us
the head of a mafia boss

252
00:11:59,177 --> 00:12:00,678
that even Kira himself couldn't kill,

253
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:02,972
why the hell would he even
need the notebook to begin with?

254
00:12:04,224 --> 00:12:06,184
[Mello] It's not just the notebook
I'm after.

255
00:12:06,309 --> 00:12:08,436
I want to eliminate my competition.

256
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:09,437
[cracks]

257
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:11,773
I will be the best!

258
00:12:12,774 --> 00:12:14,192
I don't care what it takes.

259
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:16,945
I will beat Near by any means necessary.

260
00:12:57,652 --> 00:12:58,945
[panting]

261
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:00,530
[man chuckles] Yeah, that's right.

262
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:02,907
-[laughter]
-[Pedro] B-- Boss!

263
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,867
Shut up!
Can't you see that I'm busy.

264
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:06,077
I’m sorry.

265
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:08,329
But Eddie and I were
talking for a minute and...

266
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:11,124
Looks like Takimura hung himself
with his tie somehow.

267
00:13:12,709 --> 00:13:14,002
What's wrong with you?

268
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:15,003
Just great!

269
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:17,046
What are we supposed to do
with a dead hostage?

270
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,549
-No, this'll be just fine.
-Huh?

271
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:22,427
If Kira is responsible for this,

272
00:13:22,552 --> 00:13:25,638
we know he can't touch us
since he doesn't know our names or faces.

273
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:28,308
That's why he went after Takimura instead.

274
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:31,728
That means Kira is someone
who knows about the kidnapping.

275
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:35,064
That should make things
rather... interesting.

276
00:13:37,692 --> 00:13:39,319
[Glen] So, what are we gonna do, Mello?

277
00:13:39,444 --> 00:13:41,237
I'll tell you what are we gonna do.

278
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:44,115
We're gonna kidnap
Soichiro Yagami's daughter,

279
00:13:44,282 --> 00:13:45,491
Sayu Yagami

280
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:52,165
[Mogi] We still haven't been able
to find any leads

281
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:54,667
on either Director Takimura
or the kidnappers

282
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:56,127
Things are getting pretty weird

283
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:58,588
I mean, they should've contacted us
by now with further demands

284
00:13:58,671 --> 00:13:59,672
but still nothing.

285
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,299
We know one thing.

286
00:14:01,424 --> 00:14:04,719
I found out the real name
of the FBI agent John McEnroe.

287
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:08,306
According to his personnel file
he is actually called Larry Conners.

288
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:09,724
[Light] Well, that's good to know.

289
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:11,476
He's also a genuine agent.

290
00:14:11,601 --> 00:14:13,603
His background and credentials check out.

291
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:14,562
On top of that,

292
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:18,191
the director of the FBI has offered
to help us rescue Director Takimura.

293
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,485
I'm pretty sure
we'll be able to trust them.

294
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:23,112
But the director should
already by dead by now.

295
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,823
Why haven't the kidnappers
said anything?

296
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:27,825
Are they gonna give up on the deal

297
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:29,827
just because they lost
their bargaining chip?

298
00:14:30,078 --> 00:14:32,413
I didn't think our opponents
would be such pushovers!

299
00:14:33,748 --> 00:14:35,792
Remember, Dad, and the rest of you too,

300
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,835
we're gonna have to be
extremely careful.

301
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,797
The director might not have known
about the notebook,

302
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,216
but he does know
who was originally working with L.

303
00:14:43,466 --> 00:14:45,009
It's possible the kidnappers

304
00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:46,969
-might come after us.
-[Misa] Hey, Light!

305
00:14:47,095 --> 00:14:48,054
[men] Huh?

306
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:51,891
I'll be a good girl
and go to bed by myself, okay?

307
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:54,894
[Light] Yeah, good night.

308
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,771
Good night, everyone!

309
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:59,857
-Guess I'll hang out around here.
-[gasps]

310
00:15:00,358 --> 00:15:02,985
It just occurred to me.
We're not the only ones in danger here.

311
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:04,821
-Our families are at risk.
-[phone ringing]

312
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:06,906
[Yagami] A call
from the director's cell phone.

313
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,658
It must be the kidnappers!

314
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:11,285
-Quick, Aizawa!
-Got it! Tracing!

315
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:16,332
This is Yagami.

316
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:20,086
[Mello] Look. About trading the director
in exchange for the notebook,

317
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:21,796
the deal's been cancelled.

318
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,506
Takimura is dead.

319
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:26,300
-[all] Huh?
-[Yagami] You bastards! What did you do?

320
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:28,594
[Mello] It's only canceled, though,
regarding the director.

321
00:15:28,678 --> 00:15:30,096
The new deal is this:

322
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:32,348
the notebook for Sayu Yagami.

323
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:34,559
[gasping]

324
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:39,397
See, as you're the deputy director
of the Japanese police,

325
00:15:39,522 --> 00:15:42,066
it would be stupid to ask you
not to call the cops.

326
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:44,944
But you had better handle this
on your own, without backup.

327
00:15:45,153 --> 00:15:47,530
If I see the police making
any big movements

328
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:50,158
in the next little while,
I'll kill your daughter.

329
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:53,411
That's right, just as easily
as we killed the director.

330
00:15:53,619 --> 00:15:56,914
I'll send you a photo of Takimura's corpse
to prove I mean business.

331
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,583
Take a good look.

332
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:00,543
-I'll contact you tomorrow.
-[call ends]

333
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,295
Huh? Wait!

334
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,464
Damn! They got me.

335
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:07,675
They used the director's death
as an opportunity to get to Sayu.

336
00:16:07,842 --> 00:16:09,677
[cackles]

337
00:16:10,178 --> 00:16:12,472
Looks like things
are getting interesting again.

338
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:13,890
Sir, I...

339
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:15,016
I...

340
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:17,268
-can't believe they'd go this far.
-Damn them!

341
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,603
YAGAMI

342
00:16:18,686 --> 00:16:20,605
-[phone ringing]
-[Sachiko] Yes, yes, coming.

343
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:23,858
Darling, you usually never call
from your work phone.

344
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,318
Is something the matter?

345
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,737
Huh? Sayu?

346
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,447
I don't know.

347
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:32,366
Well, now that you mention it,
she is late getting home.

348
00:16:33,284 --> 00:16:34,285
Sayu…

349
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:35,536
[phone buzzing]

350
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:36,579
BIG BROTHER

351
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:42,293
Dad, are you okay?

352
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:46,047
I've just realized something.

353
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:48,132
I think it was Kira
who killed the director,

354
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:49,383
not the kidnappers.

355
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:50,510
[men] Huh?

356
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:54,180
He probably did it because he doesn't want
the notebook to fall into the wrong hands.

357
00:16:54,347 --> 00:16:56,182
Kira claims to be justice.

358
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:59,393
He wouldn't want the notebook
used by someone evil.

359
00:16:59,977 --> 00:17:01,312
If he killed the director,

360
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:02,522
then it's reasonable to assume

361
00:17:02,605 --> 00:17:05,900
he has ways of obtaining information
from within the police force.

362
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,694
That means we should be the ones
who investigate this.

363
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:10,112
We leave the police out of it.

364
00:17:10,488 --> 00:17:11,572
Otherwise...

365
00:17:11,906 --> 00:17:14,784
Kira will find out about it
and probably kill the hostage.

366
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:16,911
Right. And we can't take that chance.

367
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,121
[cackles]

368
00:17:23,918 --> 00:17:24,877
[Rester] Near...

369
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:26,462
we've just received a report

370
00:17:26,546 --> 00:17:28,548
that the director
of the Japanese Police Agency

371
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:29,715
has been killed.

372
00:17:29,924 --> 00:17:32,635
-[Near] I see. By whom?
-"By whom?"

373
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:35,137
Uh... The kidnappers, of course. Who else?

374
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:36,180
It would be interesting

375
00:17:36,264 --> 00:17:37,723
-if it turned out to be Kira.
-Huh?

376
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:39,475
[Near] That's a very good point.

377
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:41,227
The police won't be
trading their notebook

378
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:42,436
if the hostage is dead,

379
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:43,938
so it protects Kira's interests.

380
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,815
And if it is in fact Kira,

381
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:48,651
I can narrow down
our list of suspects significantly.

382
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,777
Huh?

383
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,905
By the way, Commander Rester…

384
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:55,283
Have you been able
to determine his whereabouts yet?

385
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:56,742
Not yet.

386
00:17:56,951 --> 00:18:00,329
We're able to confirm that he
left the institution four years ago.

387
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:02,248
But nothing beyond that.

388
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:05,668
-Very well. That clinches it.
-What?

389
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,796
[Near] Mello, you never change.

390
00:18:08,963 --> 00:18:10,881
You always overlook
the most important things

391
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:13,593
because you let your emotions
get the better of you.

392
00:18:13,843 --> 00:18:16,929
Or perhaps you're not even
involved in this case.

393
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:20,433
How could you leave your photo
behind at the orphanage?

394
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,644
[phone ringing]

395
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,605
This is Yagami.

396
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:28,149
[Mello] Your daughter has finally arrived.
It's about time.

397
00:18:28,316 --> 00:18:29,317
What you mean?

398
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:32,403
[Mello] You already have a pretty
good idea of where we are, don't you?

399
00:18:32,612 --> 00:18:33,738
Hmm...

400
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:35,323
[Mello] We'll make the exchange here.

401
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:37,867
Come to LA by yourself in two days,

402
00:18:38,034 --> 00:18:40,703
and of course,
bring the notebook with you.

403
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:43,122
[Yagami] I won't make the trade
unless I'm sure my daughter is safe.

404
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:45,249
I want to talk to her right now!

405
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:47,877
[Mello] How about this?
I'll send you another photo.

406
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:49,295
That should satisfy you.

407
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,546
-[call ends]
-[murmurs nervously]

408
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:52,006
[both murmur nervously]

409
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:53,966
[phone beeps]

410
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:57,136
[whimpers] Oh! Sayu!

411
00:19:00,765 --> 00:19:03,934
Hey, Chief, we've narrowed the call down
to Fifth Street in LA.

412
00:19:04,352 --> 00:19:07,021
[Light] I just checked out the show
that was playing in the background

413
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:10,358
And it's being broadcast right now
on a local LA station.

414
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:13,527
They must've shown us that
so we'd know the photo is recent.

415
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:15,946
Oh, thank goodness.

416
00:19:16,739 --> 00:19:19,575
At least we know she's still alive.
That's reassuring.

417
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,078
Hmm.

418
00:19:23,371 --> 00:19:25,373
I'm taking the notebook to Los Angeles.

419
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:28,668
It's my decision, both as deputy director
of the Japanese Police Force

420
00:19:28,793 --> 00:19:30,461
and as Sayu Yagami's father!

421
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:32,713
I'll take full responsibility
for the consequences.

422
00:19:32,797 --> 00:19:33,964
That's my final word.

423
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:37,093
Wait, Dad. Before we do anything,
we have to come up with a plan.

424
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:38,761
He's right, Chief. We can't rush in.

425
00:19:38,928 --> 00:19:41,097
But I have to be in LA in two days.

426
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:42,640
We don't have time.

427
00:19:47,937 --> 00:19:50,481
So what you're telling me
is that Kira killed Takimura,

428
00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:51,941
not the kidnappers?

429
00:19:52,108 --> 00:19:54,610
I'm simply putting it forward
as a possibility.

430
00:19:54,694 --> 00:19:56,112
If it does turn out to be true,

431
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:58,030
then it means Kira must be
getting his information

432
00:19:58,114 --> 00:19:59,448
from the Japanese police.

433
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:00,741
Hmm.

434
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,412
-[phone ringing]
-[grunts]

435
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:06,664
-[phone beeps]
-Yes?

436
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,040
-[Light in distorted voice] This is L.
-Huh?

437
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,000
I don't believe it.

438
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:11,085
It's L.

439
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:15,297
I've already heard what investigator
John McEnroe, or rather Larry Conners,

440
00:20:15,423 --> 00:20:17,216
had to say to Deputy Director Yagami

441
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:19,301
in regards to the notebook
in the Kira case.

442
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:21,804
Will you help us
with the investigation

443
00:20:21,929 --> 00:20:24,223
into NPA director Takimura's murder?

444
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,850
I see. Well...

445
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,309
Pass me the phone.

446
00:20:27,727 --> 00:20:29,812
-[rattling over phone]
-Huh?

447
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:35,943
I'm pleased to meet you at last,
L number two.

448
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,698
[grunts]

449
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:42,408
"Number two?"

450
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,452
-What do you mean by that?
-[men] Huh?

451
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:45,745
Who is this?

452
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:48,205
There's really no point
in trying to hide it.

453
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,875
We are a new organization
known as the SPK,

454
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,543
or "Special Provision for Kira".

455
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:54,628
It was established
to find and capture Kira

456
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:56,005
without the help of L.

457
00:20:56,547 --> 00:20:58,549
[in distorted voice]
Furthermore, seven of our top members

458
00:20:58,674 --> 00:20:59,967
already know of L's death.

459
00:21:00,885 --> 00:21:01,969
[Light] They do?

460
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:04,346
Where'd they hear that?
Who the hell told them?

461
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:05,848
As for myself,

462
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:08,058
I'm at the center of the SPK.

463
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:10,269
You can address me...

464
00:21:10,644 --> 00:21:11,604
as N.

465
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:13,230
[Light] N?

466
00:21:13,689 --> 00:21:14,899
Who is this guy?

467
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:16,525
Is he joking?

468
00:21:17,466 --> 00:21:18,444
But…

469
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:20,112
[chains rattling]

470
00:21:20,196 --> 00:21:23,866
...this strange feeling, what is it?

471
00:21:26,535 --> 00:21:32,208
TO BE CONTINUED

472
00:21:35,795 --> 00:21:38,881
[theme music plays]
